MediCore Chatbot
This is a Flask-based web application for a mental health chatbot named MediCore. Follow the steps below to set up and run the application.

Prerequisites
Make sure you have Python installed on your machine. You will also need to install Flask and OpenAI Python packages.

Installation
    Clone or download the project folder to your local machine.

Open a terminal and navigate to the project directory.

Run the following command in the terminal to install the necessary Python packages:
    pip install flask openai


Folder Structure
    Ensure the folder structure looks like this:

            MediCore-Chatbot/
            │
            ├── app.py  # Main Flask application file
            ├── templates/
            │   └── index.html  # HTML file for the chat interface
            ├── static/
            │   ├── style.css  # CSS file for styling
            │   └── images/
            │       └── Group Logo.jpg  # Logo image used in the chat interface
            └── README.md  # This README file

Running the Application
  To run the Flask application:

  In the terminal, navigate to the project directory if you haven't already.
  
  Run the following command:
    python 'name of the python file'.py
